Key Match Events: Hakim Ziyech scored the opening goal for Morocco in the 37th minute.
Achraf Hakimi scored the second goal for Morocco in the 81st minute.
Pre-Game Insights: The match is a crucial finale to Group F in the Africa Cup of Nations, with qualification for the round of 16 at stake.
Zambia is returning to the AFCON stage after a three-edition absence and is still chasing their first win since their 2012 triumph.
Zambia faces a win-or-bust scenario against Morocco, having only beaten Morocco once in six meetings.
Morocco is widely tipped as the tournament's strongest contenders and is targeting their second AFCON title in history.
